This post assumes you&rsquo;re already familiar with OpenTelemetry, and are already collecting some observability data.
Whether you&rsquo;ve chosen automatic instrumentation, or manual, you&rsquo;re now collecting telemetry data from your code. Congratulations &#x1f389;
But what about all the other code you&rsquo;re using? When your service makes a database query, or fetches weather data, you&rsquo;re using someone else&rsquo;s code. These other services may have their own production problems - can you separate issues in your code from issues in a dependency with your current observability signals?
